  "response_text": "The commercial opens in a sunlit orange grove. A full, rounded orange tree stands in the center, heavy with bright orange fruit among dense green leaves. Other trees frame it on both sides, and pale grassy hills stretch across the background under a clear blue sky. The light is warm and golden, giving the orchard a calm, fresh morning feeling.\n\nA bottle of Simply Orange appears outdoors beside an orange tree. On the left, leafy branches hang close to the foreground with whole oranges still on the tree. On the right, the orange juice bottle stands upright on a flat surface, filled with deep orange juice and topped with a dark green cap. Its front label clearly reads “Simply Orange,” with an orange illustration and a small red banner that says “Pulp Free.” Whole oranges and a cut orange half sit beside the bottle, the cut side facing forward so the juicy orange segments are visible.\n\nThe view moves into close details of oranges growing on the tree. A single ripe orange hangs beneath glossy green leaves, its textured peel catching the sunlight. Tiny droplets cling to the leaves and fruit. More oranges appear clustered among branches, partly hidden by leaves, with soft golden light filtering through the foliage. The fruit looks natural and unhandled, still attached to the tree, surrounded by green leaves and branches.\n\nThe orchard is then shown more broadly again, with rows of orange trees loaded with fruit. Sunbeams stream through the branches, lighting the grass below and making the oranges glow against the dark trunks and shaded leaves. The trees fill the scene from side to side, emphasizing abundance: dozens of oranges hang at different heights, some in full sunlight, others tucked into shadow.\n\nA close-up returns to a single orange hanging from a branch. As it rests under overlapping leaves, the words “Simply Orange” gradually appear over the surface of the orange as a transparent graphic, as if the brand name is being associated directly with the fruit. This image blends into the final product display.\n\nAt the end, two Simply Orange bottles stand in the foreground on a wooden-looking surface, set against a softly blurred orchard background filled with orange trees. The larger bottle is on the right and dominates the scene; its label reads “Simply Orange,” with “Pulp Free” at the top and “Not From Concentrate” below. A smaller bottle stands to its left with the same brand name and a green cap. Around the bottles are whole oranges and a halved orange, again facing forward to show its bright, juicy interior. In the upper left, white on-screen text appears: “Honestly Simple.” Near the bottom right, small white text reads “Gently Pasteurized.” A small Facebook icon and partial Facebook web address appear at the bottom left. The final image holds on the bottles, oranges, and orchard, with the product visually presented as simple orange juice connected directly to fresh oranges.",
